  "body": "### Description\n\nIt was brought to my attention that users that need to use an Openshift ImageStream (e.g a builder image) from another namespace have difficulties as we currently have no way of expressing this need.\r\n\r\nIt appears that this is something one can do when defining the ImageStream manually, but not possible when using the `quarkus-openshift` extension.\r\n\r\nA workaround is to use the full image (internal registry, repo and tag), but this may require RBAC recofniguration as in once case user reads streams, while in the other image stream tags.\r\n\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
